description: From Latin catalecticus, from Ancient Greek καταληκτικός (katalēktikós, “leaving off, incomplete”) from κατά (katá, “down, wholly”) + ληκτικός (lēktikós, “causing to stop”).

entries.meaning: (poetry) (said of a line with incomplete meter) lacking a syllable at the end or ending with an incomplete foot.
incomplete; partial; not affecting the whole of a substance
examples: The process is not practised to any extent , but is a curious example of a catalectic action started by the impact of light

entries.meaning: (poetry) A line with incomplete meter, lacking a syllable at the end or ending with an incomplete foot.
